The paper focuses on developing an algorithm for AUC optimization, which is a common performance measure in machine learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of regression-based algorithms and low rank matrices to efficiently handle high dimensional data, which are common techniques in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the need to maintain statistics of the training data, which is related to Data Structures (cs.DS) and Statistics (cs.ST) sub-categories.
